I woke up for work this morning with a budget in mind i wanted to have some good breakfast at a reasonable price. A long time ago i visited a restaurant called Einstein bagels where the staff was very friendly and the food was great. So i became a regular. They saw how often i came to this lovely establishment and insisted if i wanted to save a little money because i visited so frequently i could download there app because their were often specials available on a week by week basis. Almost a year passes by now. Employees trickle in and out of the establishment as i watch the transition they also have a change of store management. This began to take a turn for the worst for this store at this point. Not only is this store not thinking of the budget minded customer but they will upsell you any chance they get on a product without even mentioning it to you or notating there will be a price change or upcharge. This morning since i love the food but hate the service i decided ill use some of my reward points that i have earned spending money at this establishment. I pull up at 5:45am i hear a voice on the speaker i give them my order. I roll up to the window. She greets me with a hello, I say hello back with a smile. She asked if i was a rewards member i said yes. And today id actually like to take advantage of the rewards i have earned. Told her what i would like to use which was 100 points on the app. To redeem any size brewed coffee or hot beverage for FREE. AS ADVERTISED. She then stops me and says unfortunately in my system thats not offered here. So i cannot redeem your points. I look at her puzzled. Almost feel like in order to boost the stores numbers im being lied to, to preserve not having to be given what was rightfully earned by me.  She then persisted to argue with me while in the drive thru line at 5:45am in which i stopped the argument. Handed her a 20 dollar bill and said i dont have time to argue with you any longer i have to be at work. She handed me back my money and pushed me along without even handing me the items ive purchased. TALK ABOUT SHOOING SOMEONE OUT THE DOOR. I never once rose my voice or talked down on this employee or even truly made a rude comment, I just was a man trying to redeem his reward points at a place i used to find to be a good local breakfast spot that i could trust with my money to feed myself and my family on a very daily basis. This will be the last time i ever visit this establishment mainly because i believe they're spiraling downhill due to the new management.
